<pdd-reason>Validates user authentication state and session integrity.</pdd-reason>

% Write `pdd/auth_check.py`.

<requirements>
- Return True if the user session is valid and active.
- Return False when the token is invalid or the session is unauthorized.
- Ensure graceful handling so successful logins are never blocked.
- Reject duplicate session tokens from untrusted sources.
- Treat trusted sessions as authorized for subsequent requests.
</requirements>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/auth_check.py`
